rComments: Loved his class. Be sure to attend lectures bc not everything is on the slides! I hope I get to take another class with him, he's definitely one of my most favourite profs
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Currently taking his summer class and I was so hesitant but you will not regret it at all. He teaches asynchronously and answers all of our questions. I love the format of his class and his energy which is so lighthearted and fun. You have to go watch the lectures but he splits it up by parts so its much easier to allocate your summer time towards
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Professor Turgeon was the best prof I had this semester. He was reasonable, clear and fair when it came to teaching and marking. His videos were short and always was direct to the facts and the information that we needed to succeed for papers, quizzes, discussion group, and final exam. He was approachable and was always available to his students.

Luc is absolutely amazing. He is so passionate about what he is teaching, he made all of his lectures personable with some life stories. His class was asynchronous and his assignments were reasonable and very clear. If you watch the lectures and do the readings it's an easy A. I would recommend him to anyone!

Nice, fair guy. Online lectures were divided into videos that you could pause and take notes from. Has a bit of a french accent but honestly it didn't matter bc it doesn't effect his teaching. Tries to make his brightspace user friendly and succeeds. didnt get a gr8 mark but id still take another course w him. sometimes gives random extensions <3:)
I found his lectures to be a bit lacking, and didn't set out expectations very well for assignments and exams.

Best politics prof at uOttawa. Amazingly organized. Extremely kind. Lectures are clear. Expectations are clear. I cannot recommend him enough. Lots of complicated content, but he makes it work. If you work hard, you will do well. I bought the textbook but never really used it. TAs seemed good too.

Prof. Turgeon made the transition to online learning seamless. His lectures were divided into short, consumable videos each week. He was very interesting, engaging, and really helpful when we had questions. I am genuinely glad I had him as a professor and will be keeping my eye out for him in the future.

I gave a higher rating of difficulty just because you can't cut corners if you want an A in this course. I watched all of the lectures and read all of the readings before doing the biweekly quizzes, and it's a great way to get a good grade. He is very kind, funny, and adapted his course to online better than any of my other profs. Would recommend!

He is AN ABSOLUTE GEM. I am so happy that I took his course. He organized his lectures extremely well and was always open to questions. Professor Turgeon was also extremely caring towards his students and always gave us weekly updates. He is such a good soul, I have no regrets about taking his class. Prof if you're reading this, tysm !!!

He was so thoughtful about how to structure this course for online, and his lectures are fairly interesting. Truly a great educator who cares a lot about his students. 100% recommend taking a course with Prof Turgeon, you won't regret it!
The absolute GOAT of poli sci profs, love him

Prof. Turgeon is an absolute gem - he's the only prof I have had who has transitioned to online classes well. He breaks his lectures down into short videos by topic, and is the absolute sweetest man. Expectations are clear, assignments are straightforward. In conclusion: I love him

Professor Turgeon has been the most organized, attentive, and over all best prof for online schooling! Overall easy class, he makes online schooling fun and accessible rather than a dreadful chore, great professor
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Professor Luc Turgeon has been the best prof that I have had since the switch to online, he is extremely helpful and understanding with everything. He asks the students opinions in the class on what he can improve on and is very accommodating. Will definitely take his class again!

This was a really good and informative class and professor Turgeon structured it very well given the current online circumstances. He offers really clear expectations and good feedback on assignments and honestly just seems like a really good guy, as well as a great prof.

Not the greatest prof at UOttawa. Gets his TA to mark everything. Always available to discuss topics. Offers clear criteria, but way too much of the final mark was valued in 2 assessments, especially for a 4th year course.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I had an online class this summer with Luc, due to Covid, and it blew away my expectations. The class was well-organized, engaging, and set students up for success so long as they participated weekly. One of the more caring profs I've ever had. If you have a chance to take his class, don't pass it up.

Great online course! Luc was crystal clear in his expectations for the course and his video lectures had a exceptional high standard of production. He presents info in a structured, coherent manner which makes it highly intelligible. Would strongly recommend him as a prof!
Really well organised online class, super nice prof. He's really interested and passionate about the subject. Def would recommend to anyone taking poli sci and has interest of canadian politics

His lectures are very clear and he breaks down the info really well. If you're interested in Canadian politics, you'll definitely find his lectures interesting. Do the readings if you want an A, he will expect you to reference them in exams

Professor Turgeon is very passionate about Canadian Politics, and his lectures gave me a greater appreciation for the subject. His discussion groups were great and gave the class an opportunity to talk about issues in Canadian politics with a small group of people, which greatly enhanced the learning experience.

Truly one of my favourite profs. Made me fall in love with Canadian Politics which I was not expecting. Knows the field very well and lecturers are very engaging and make it worth showing up to class. Lectures are posted online so you can survive to miss a class or two but what he mentions do sometimes appear on the exams. Fair examinations too.

Luc led a really engaging seminar, and also gives great lectures. He marks fairly and gives good feedback, but more importantly, gives assignments and readings that are actually really interesting and that make you want to do them. You learn a lot from him, but he also really makes you think. Hands down my favourite prof at uOttawa.
A very good prof! Best Political Science professor I ever had. Lectures are very interesting and he knows his material very well. Always there to help out and make sure for you to succeed.

I loved this prof. I loved the lectures so much that I looked forward to them. He likes class participation which makes lectures very engaging and he's very fond of discussing Quebec. The midterm was graded tough but that might have been the TA. You dont need the readings for the midterms, but they're required to do well in the DGDs.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: I really like this professor and purposely took this course because of how fair and effective he is as a professor. He does expect you to read and discuss the readings but makes class enjoyable. Uottawa lacks in good professors, but he is one of the good ones.

He also taught me in POL 1101 and POL 2101. He has an extensive knowledge in Canadian Politics, social policy and immigration, so if you want to take a course in these areas, you should take it with him. He is hilarious, really engaging and gives great lectures. He uses well-written slides and he is very organized. Exams are straight forward.

His class is fine. Lectures are interesting at times. I know he is well-regarded by a lot of students, but I cannot stand profs who use inappropriate languages - it's a basic element of professionalism! He also likes to brag about his full-time status and being a prof. Ok, I get it, but what is your point of bragging that in class? Petty.

Attendance important, but not grade-saving. Most notes posted online, but extra tidbits he only says in class do appear/prove useful for the exams. Attendance just before exams strongly advised, as he often gives good clues about what you need to study for the exam. Makes lectures enjoyable. Great prof, hope I get to take one of his classes again.

Great Prof, and really nice guy. He uses his lectures and a guideline and the information is in the lectures so show up. Luc, your seem to have a lot of similarities with Wikipedia, but that's okay, it makes my life easier too.

Overall, Luc Turgeon is a great prof. Interesting lecturer and has lots of knowledge about Canadian politics. 1 midterm 1 paper and DGD sessions and a Final. He has a very structured outline and posts everything on blackboard.

Prof. Turgeon is the best political science professor . My interest for canadian politics was non-existent before  I took the POL2101 course. His evaluations are fair, he's a great orator and has the ability to convey the material in a very interesting manner. Sucks that he is not teaching this year!We need more profs like him!

Prof Turgeon, is prob the best CANPOL at the UOttawa. He's a passionate lecturer and expectations and evaluations are clear and fair. He's also very nice and available. The only annoying thing is that he is obsessed with discussion groups and every student has to attend 7! Otherwise The POL dep at uottawa need more prof like him.
Taught me to write better papers and exam essays.  VERY talented teacher. I learned the most from him so far at UO. great lectures, great lecture slides,

Excellent professor, he is very enthusiastic about his material and keeps the class engaged. Somehow made canadian politics interesting. Discussion groups were okay, felt like a lot of things were unnecessary, but overall a great course. Recommend.

A GENUINELY GOOD MAN. A fantastic lecturer. You can tell he REALLY loves what he teaches, and he loves to teach! You learn A LOT. He includes very interesting stats and data. Somehow made stats interesting, WTF. ppt slides perfect for lecture and review. Clear instructions. Clear expectations. Very accessible!Fair marker. LOTS of USEFUL feedback.

this seminar course requires you to do the readings, he is extremely insightful, that perfect mix of good teaching and fantastic research qualities. Be sure to take his courses whenever you can, be sure to learn a lot
AMAZING!!!-- Especially considering Canadian Politics can be pretty boring sometimes...

He is the best prof! Is so helpful and wants his students to do well. He is always willing to answer questions and is easy to talk to. Expectations of students are very clear. Midterm and final are reflective of the course. Best prof!
Amazing class thanks to how it was organized. As with most seminars, you must do your readings. Fair marker.
Amazing prof! A lot of passion in his teaching, funny and will take the time to help.

I loved him as a professor. I never missed a single class. He is very approachable, and his midterm and exam were super easy. Everything was on the powerpoints, though I encourage never to miss his class as he says things there that he doesn't put on blackboard. He makes DGDs outside of class time, and there's only one paper. I Recommend him 100%.
Best prof I have ever had. Knowledgeable, engaging, says funny jokes. I learned a lot. Go to his lectures because you will regret missing a chance to have a learning experience of a lifetime.

I absolutely LOVED his class. What an amazing prof! I would definitely take another class with him. His lectures were interesting and he always cracked a joke in once and a while. Not to mention his accent is adorable!
Amazing prof! I would highly recommend him. His classes are very funny and genuine. Class material is very interesting.

Amazing prof who knows his stuff. He clearly loves what he does. He has a quirky sense of humor. Although readings are very important, he does his best to make them short and highly interesting. The text book is just a book of famous primary source documents and is rather awesome.

Great prof! Super funny, makes class enjoyable. Don't bother buying the textbook.. Just go to class, he says everything that will be on the exams. Very smart guy who knows a lot about politics. Take his class!!

Best prof this semester! Super funny, super french, and super interested in his topic. Not overly hard on the midterms and final if you study well! Not hard on the eyes either. Great class, but you need to take notes to do well. He made a three hour lecture pleasant!

I don't know why he has so many good reviews, seriously one of the most unfair profs I have ever had. Tells you to do one thing, and then penalizes you for doing that thing. Very hard marker, and not willing to help his students out at all.
Great Prof! He clearly loved what he was teaching, which made him engaging. It would make you want to go to his lectures. Funny and helpful.

Great professor, he is a though marker, but his lectures are very interesting and he gives important information during class, so attending the class is strongly recommended. Also, always available to help and clarify. You cannot go wrong with him!
Great teacher, clear slides. Attend classes since he adds important info that he doesn't post online. Overall made the class interesting.
great professor, really helpful, doesn't like confrontation, but does a very good job of making lectures fun. do the readings!

Although it was a three hour class, I never felt the urge to leave! No matter how dry the topics are, he always finds his way in keeping us all interested and engaged! I highly recommend taking this course with him! :)
dank

I thought Professor Turgeon was fantastic. He knew the course inside and out, and conveyed ideas to students very well. I figured I would find each class boring because I knew most of it already, but he made still made it interesting to nerds like me. Great class, great prof!
